com.hazelcast.query.extractor

Class ArgumentParser<I,O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hazelcast.query.extractor.ArgumentParser<I,O>
  • Type Parameters:
    I - type of the unparsed argument object (input)
    O - type of the parsed argument object (output)
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultArgumentParser

    public abstract class ArgumentParser<I,O>
extends Object
    Common superclass for all argument parsers.

    For now, it's not possible to register a custom ArgumentParser, thus a default parser is used. It follows a "pass-through" semantics, which means that the string located in the square-brackets is passed "as-is" to the extract method.

    It is not allowed to use square brackets within the argument string.
